  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ingwavuma Orphan Care &amp; Home Based Care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">KwaZulu-Natal province in South Africa has one of the highest rates of HIV in the world, with an estimated 29% of adults living with HIV. Improved access to antiretroviral therapy has helped those receiving treatment to return to good health, but there is still a need to support people to continue their treatment, and provide care for orphaned children and people that are bedridden. FOTCHSA provides home-based care to people who are bedridden, support groups for people with HIV, couples counselling, and practical and emotional support for orphans and vulnerable children. As a result of the project, thousands of people living with and affected by HIV will have access to prevention and care and support services, and local partners will have a clear plan to make their work more sustainable in the future.</narrative>
  </description>
